===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} ''[[mortier]]'', from {{etyl|la|en}} ''[[mortarium]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|ɔː(r)tə(r)|lang=en}}
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈmɔːtɘ(ɹ)/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-us-mortar.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} A mixture of [[lime]] or [[cement]], [[sand]] and [[water]] used for [[bonding]] [[brick]]s and [[stone]]s.
# {{context|countable|military|lang=en}} A muzzle-loading, [[indirect]] fire [[weapon]] with a tube length of 10 to 20 [[caliber]]s and designed to lob [[shell]]s at very steep [[trajectories]].
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A hollow [[vessel]] used to [[pound]], [[crush]], [[rub]], [[grind]] or [[mix]] [[ingredient]]s with a [[pestle]].

